event: When I was younger, I was in the Boy Scouts, and we went camping all the time. One year, we went to Yellowstone or Yosemite, and I worked on a mountain biking merit badge. It was intense and fun, going downhill at about forty-five miles an hour in dirt on a bicycle. I'll never forget that experience.
